properties.Name: Policyholder
properties.Description:
A person, company, organization or institution that owns a life insurance policy and is responsible for making all the changes in the policy. 

This is usually the insured person, but it may also be a relative of the insured, a partnership or a corporation. 

The policyholder is the party protected in case of a loss or claim.

Columns.Name: PolicyholderId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Policyholder.

Columns.Name: ThirdPartyApplicantIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the policy was applied for by a third party other than the policyholder.

Columns.Name: PartyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Party.
